Weekly TODO.md regeneration, Sunday 03:15 AM ET. Runs AFTER the 03:00 Drive gardener / log-rotate and BEFORE the 03:45 sync-to-air (the 30-min margin is deliberate — finish writing TODO.md well before sync-to-air rsyncs it to the Air). You regenerate the daemon-facing `TODO.md` from its canonical sources.

**Why this job exists (read this — it's the whole point):** `TODO.md` used to be regenerated by Cowork-Iris's weekly "vault gardener," which only fires while the Cowork app is open on the Mini. It silently missed on 6/7, 6/8, and 6/14 — leaving `TODO.md` stale for days. `TODO.md` is the worst artifact to lose because **it loads into the daemon's per-message prompt** (`iris.py` `TODO_FILE`), so a stale TODO actively misinforms every Telegram interaction. launchd fires regardless of any app being open, so this re-host removes that single point of failure. (The Cowork vault gardener may still touch other things; this job owns TODO.md specifically.)

Read `_Iris_Memory/Sessions/CLAUDE_CODE_HANDOFF.md` (latest entry) for context. Hard rules from `06_CEO/Designs/2026-05-26_Claude_Code_Engineering_Handoff.md` apply. Stay strictly in the engineering-side-car role.

## What TODO.md is

`TODO.md` is the compact, auto-generated "project picture" that loads into the daemon's prompt. It is a DERIVED rollup — never the source of truth. It must stay compact (it costs daemon tokens every message). Do NOT hand-add new facts; only summarize what already exists in the canonical sources below.

## Canonical sources (read ALL of these, in order)

1. `INBOX.md` — this week's actions + TODAY items (the `## 📌 TODAY` and `## 🧍 THIS WEEK` sections, plus the C2 stale-on-you fenced block).
2. `06_CEO/Decision_Queue.md` — pending decisions / open rows + AUTO-deadlines.
3. `BRANDS/3SK_Finance/Launch_Runway.md` — production track / video pipeline state.
4. `BRANDS/3SK_Finance/Launch_Scorecard.md` — metrics / weekly velocity.
5. `06_CEO/Designs/2026-05-26_Phase_4_and_5_Build_Queue.md` (+ any other `06_CEO/Designs/*Build_Queue*`) — engineering build state.

## How to regenerate

Rewrite `TODO.md` in place, preserving its existing structure so the daemon prompt stays stable. Keep these sections (drop one only if it has genuinely nothing live):
- A one-line generated-file header (see format rule below).
- `## 🎯 North star` — the standing 5-year line (carry it forward verbatim from the current TODO.md; it does not change week to week).
- `## 🔥 Critical path (legal/financial chain)` — the live legal/financial dependency chain, pulled from INBOX TODAY + Decision_Queue. Use relative-free dating: write absolute dates (e.g. `6/21`), never "TODAY" without a date — stale "TODAY" with no date is exactly the bug this job fixes.
- `## 🎬 Production track (the actual bottleneck)` — from Launch_Runway + Launch_Scorecard.
- `## ⚖️ Pending decisions` — a one-line pointer to Decision_Queue with the open-row count + any imminent AUTO-deadlines.

**Header format (REQUIRED — keep the generated-file warning):** the first lines must be:
```
# 3SK International — Project Picture (auto-generated)

_⚙️ GENERATED FILE — do not hand-edit. Regenerated weekly (Sunday) by the launchd TODO-regen job (`com.iris.claude-code-todo-regen`) from the canonical sources: [[INBOX]] · [[Decision_Queue]] · [[Launch_Runway]] · [[Launch_Scorecard]] · `06_CEO/Designs/` build queues. This regen: YYYY-MM-DD ~03:15 ET. This file loads into the daemon's prompt — kept compact by design._
```
Fill `YYYY-MM-DD` with today's ISO date. Note the source-of-regen line now names this launchd job, not the Cowork gardener.

## Write procedure (ORDER MATTERS — atomic, never a half-written TODO.md)
`TODO.md` loads into the live daemon's prompt and is rsynced to the Air at 03:45, so it must never be observed half-written. Do the write in this exact order with Bash, NOT a plain in-place rewrite:
1. **Back up:** `mkdir -p 07_Archive/todo_baks && cp TODO.md "07_Archive/todo_baks/TODO.md.bak-$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)"`.
2. **Prune the bak dir to the 15 most recent** (deterministic, not eyeballed): `ls -1t 07_Archive/todo_baks/TODO.md.bak-* 2>/dev/null | tail -n +16 | tr '\n' '\0' | xargs -0 rm -f`.
3. **Write the new content to a temp file** in the SAME directory: write to `TODO.md.tmp` (same filesystem as TODO.md — required for an atomic rename).
4. **Atomic swap:** `mv -f TODO.md.tmp TODO.md`. `mv` within one filesystem is atomic, so any reader (daemon or rsync) sees either the old or the new file, never a truncated one.
Never leave `TODO.md.tmp` behind; never leave a `.bak` in the vault root.

## Safety / discipline
- **Compact.** Target the current TODO.md length (~30-50 lines). If a section would balloon, summarize harder and link to the source with `[[wikilinks]]`.
- **Derived only.** Never invent a task or decision that isn't in a canonical source. If a source is missing/unreadable, regenerate the rest and flag the gap rather than guessing.
- Do NOT edit any canonical source. This job is read-many, write-one (`TODO.md`) + the bak.

## Output
- Rewrite `TODO.md`.
- Append ONE bullet to today's daily note `_Iris_Memory/Daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` under `## 🤖 Claude Code intra-day log`. Format: `HH:MM — TODO.md regen (launchd) → [N critical-path / M decisions / production line refreshed]`. If the daily note doesn't exist, create it from `01_Operating_Docs/Templates/Daily_Note_Template.md`. Do NOT touch Cowork's section.
- Append a bridge-file entry ONLY if a canonical source was missing/unreadable or the regen produced something surprising. A clean weekly regen skips the bridge (daily-note bullet is enough).
- Do NOT make structural iris.py changes. Do NOT install/uninstall plugins. Do NOT modify .env files. Do NOT stage or commit (the pre-brief A1 catch-all ships any commits; this job commits nothing).

---

## ⛳ Completion signal — REQUIRED LAST LINE (run_claude_job.sh reads this for Steve's Telegram alert)

After all other work and logging, the VERY LAST line of your output MUST be exactly one of:
- `ROUTINE_COMPLETE` — TODO.md regenerated, daily-note bullet written, nothing skipped.
- `ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE: <one-line reason>` — a source was missing, the regen was partial, or anything was skipped/blocked.

Output nothing after that line. This line is how Steve gets a done / not-fully-done alert on Telegram.
